President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Elaine A. McCusker of Virginia to be the Under Secretary of Defense (Comptroller). McCusker currently serves as the Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Comptroller and has previously held positions at the United States Central Command, the Office of the Under Secretary of Defense Comptroller, and the Senate Armed Services Committee. She also has experience in the private sector and academic community, working with the Department of Energy's Argonne National Laboratory and the University of Washington.